title: Viktor Yanukovych - Wikipedia
snippet: Viktor Fedorovych Yanukovych (born 9 July 1950) is a former Ukrainian politician who served as the fourth president of Ukraine from 2010 to 2014. He also served as the prime minister of Ukraine several times between 2002 and 2007 and was a member of the Verkhovna Rada (parliament) from 2006 to 2010.

title: Viktor Yanukovych | Facts, Biography, Maidan Protests, & Flight to Russia | Britannica
snippet: Viktor Yanukovych (born July 9, 1950, Yenakiyeve, Ukraine, U.S.S.R. [now in Ukraine]) is a Ukrainian politician who served as prime minister (2002–05, 2006–07) and president (2010–14) of Ukraine.

title: Former Ukrainian President Yanukovych loses court battle against EU sanctions – POLITICO
snippet: Viktor Yanukovych was the pro-Russian president of Ukraine from 2010 to 2014 before he was overthrown by the Euromaidan protests and fled to Russia.

title: Viktor Yanukovych – DW
snippet: Viktor Yanukovych is the former president of Ukraine. He served from 2010 until his ouster in February 2014, when he fled to Russia to live in exile.
